<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8"?>
<zabbix_export>
    <version>4.4</version>
    <date>2019-12-06T12:15:32Z</date>
    <groups>
        <group>
            <name>TEMPLATES</name>
        </group>
    </groups>
    <templates>
        <template>
            <template>Template OSSO dpkg</template>
            <name>Template OSSO dpkg</name>
            <groups>
                <group>
                    <name>TEMPLATES</name>
                </group>
            </groups>
            <applications>
                <application>
                    <name>dpkg</name>
                </application>
            </applications>
            <items>
                <item>
                    <name>Package updates available</name>
                    <type>ZABBIX_ACTIVE</type>
                    <key>dpkg.updates[package]</key>
                    <delay>1h</delay>
                    <trends>90d</trends>
                    <description>History (non-trend) set to 90 so we can look back with triggers</description>
                    <applications>
                        <application>
                            <name>dpkg</name>
                        </application>
                    </applications>
                    <request_method>POST</request_method>
                </item>
                <item>
                    <name>Security updates available</name>
                    <type>ZABBIX_ACTIVE</type>
                    <key>dpkg.updates[security]</key>
                    <delay>1h</delay>
                    <trends>90d</trends>
                    <description>History (non-trend) set to 90 so we can look back with triggers</description>
                    <applications>
                        <application>
                            <name>dpkg</name>
                        </application>
                    </applications>
                    <request_method>POST</request_method>
                    <triggers>
                        <trigger>
                            <expression>{$DISABLE_SEC_UPDATES}&lt;&gt;1 and&#13;
{last()}&gt;0 and&#13;
{min(61d)}&gt;0 and&#13;
{nodata(8h)}=0</expression>
                            <name>{ITEM.LASTVALUE2} security update(s) available on {HOST.NAME} for 61+d</name>
                            <description>We added the nodata-check so we don't get these next to the &quot;machine is unreachable&quot; messages.&#13;
&#13;
Unfortunately, ITEM.VALUE2 is not &quot;dpkg.updates[security].min(61d)&quot; but the &quot;value that dpkg.updates[security] had when the trigger got raised.&#13;
&#13;
And ITEM.LASTVALUE2 is the &quot;current&quot; value of &quot;dpkg.updates[security]&quot;.&#13;
&#13;
Getting the value of dpkg.updates[security].min(61d) into the trigger-name seems impossible.&#13;
&#13;
You *can* do the following, but not in the trigger-name, only in action-messages:&#13;
  {{HOST.HOST}:{ITEM.KEY2}.min(61d)}</description>
                        </trigger>
                    </triggers>
                </item>
            </items>
            <macros>
                <macro>
                    <macro>{$DISABLE_SEC_UPDATES}</macro>
                    <value>0</value>
                </macro>
            </macros>
        </template>
    </templates>
</zabbix_export>
